ions if renovations take longer than expected? Most lenders offer extension options for legitimate delays, though requirements vary."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can luxury upgrades hurt your appraisal or loan approval?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Should you worry about over-improving for your neighborhood? This legitimate concern requires thoughtful consideration during renovation planning."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How does HomeStyle Renovation financing work for multi-unit properties?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "HomeStyle loans can finance two- to four-unit properties, offering unique opportunities for owner-occupants and investors:"}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What documentation should you save during the renovation?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Why is thorough documentation critical during HomeStyle Renovation projects? Proper records protect your interests and ensure smooth processing."}}]};
